        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 12 at 5:57PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 557 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Freeland to near Marion Springs to near
Elsie. Movement was east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
St. Charles, Freeland, and Marion Springs around 605 PM EDT.
Saginaw around 610 PM EDT.
Chesaning, Zilwaukee, and Oakley around 615 PM EDT.
Bridgeport around 620 PM EDT.
Frankenmuth around 640 PM EDT.
Birch Run around 645 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by these storms include Brant, Nelson,
Carrollton, Garfield, Arthur, Fenmore, Burt, Buena Vista Township,
Gera, and Layton Corners.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
